{"id": 7, "category": "correctness", "description": "validate_result.numeric_ranges silently skips any value that is not int|float — including the str fallback that _jsonify intends to emit for high-precision Decimals (dead today, but latent), and including NUMBER values returned as Python int. More critically, bool flows through `isinstance(v, (int,float))` and triggers spurious min/max issues because True==1 in Python. With a hypothetical CASE WHEN that yields BOOLEAN-like 0/1 mixed with True from the driver, ranges flag noise.", "reproducer": "Verified: validate_result with rows [[True],[False]] and numeric_ranges F:{min:10,max:100} → ok=False, 'F=True < min=10'.", "code_ref": "text2sql_agent/tools.py:82-99", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "verified"}
{"id": 8, "category": "performance", "description": "Every agent.run() opens a fresh Oracle connection for the unconditional MIN/MAX MONTH_DT probe in _data_range_note, even for questions unrelated to time ranges, plus a new connection for every subsequent execute_sql. No pooling, no caching. On the 5-question grader this means 5 extra startup probes; on a slow XE container each probe adds seconds of latency to the user-visible CLI response.", "reproducer": "code_ref: _data_range_note unconditionally invoked from run(); each run_query opens via _connect.", "code_ref": "text2sql_agent/agent.py:74-104 + text2sql_agent/db.py:19-28", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 9, "category": "error_handling", "description": "The OpenAI client call in the agent loop has no request_timeout and no max_retries override. If Ollama hangs (model loading, long generation), each of the up to 8 steps can block indefinitely, and Ctrl-C is the only escape. The top-level except in __main__ converts the eventual exception into exit 1 but there is no soft cap.", "reproducer": "code_ref: client.chat.completions.create call passes only model/messages/tools/tool_choice/temperature.", "code_ref": "text2sql_agent/agent.py:112-118", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 10, "category": "semantics", "description": "validate_result.numeric_ranges does `break` after the first out-of-range value per column. For multi-row top-N or per-month results where multiple rows violate bounds, only one is reported; the model gets a single-issue picture and may issue a localized fix that leaves the other violations in place.", "reproducer": "code_ref: explicit `break` inside the per-row loop in numeric_ranges section.", "code_ref": "text2sql_agent/tools.py:90-99", "severity": "minor", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}
{"id": 11, "category": "correctness", "description": "execute_sql truncates results to 200 rows but the system prompt does not require the model to add ORDER BY / FETCH FIRST itself. When the model issues e.g. `SELECT ORGANIZATION_NM, PNL_SUM FROM client_product WHERE MONTH_DT = ...` (no aggregate) and the table holds thousands of rows, the agent silently feeds 200 arbitrary rows to validate / final_answer; final_answer's 'top customer' answer is taken from an unordered, truncated slice.", "reproducer": "code_ref: run_query unconditionally fetchmany(201); model-side prompt says 'ORDER BY for top-N' but the system enforces nothing.", "code_ref": "text2sql_agent/db.py:55-85", "severity": "major", "demonstrability": "reasoned"}

